From: Spike S <spike-s@fc32>
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] riscv: compat: return AUDIT_ARCH_RISCV32 for ILP32 processes

Three patches are needed to make seccomp arch-dispatch work for ILP32 processes
on RISC-V 64-bit kernels:

  1. arch/riscv/include/asm/syscall.h: check TIF_32BIT in syscall_get_arch()
  2. arch/riscv/include/asm/seccomp.h: define SECCOMP_ARCH_COMPAT for ILP32
  3. kernel/seccomp.c: skip cache for ILP32 (TIF_32BIT) processes

This patch (1/3): syscall_get_arch() unconditionally returns AUDIT_ARCH_RISCV64
on CONFIG_64BIT kernels, even when a compat (ILP32) process is running.

TIF_32BIT is set by SET_PERSONALITY() for ELFCLASS32 ELF binaries and is used
by syscall_handler() to dispatch to the compat syscall table.  Connect it to
syscall_get_arch() so that seccomp_data.arch reports AUDIT_ARCH_RISCV32.

Signed-off-by: Spike S <spike-s@fc32>

[PATCH 2/3] riscv: seccomp: define SECCOMP_ARCH_COMPAT for ILP32 processes

arch/riscv/include/asm/seccomp.h does not define SECCOMP_ARCH_COMPAT, so the
seccomp cache uses a single native bitmap without checking sd->arch.  For a
filter that allows all RISCV64 syscalls, all bits are set in the native bitmap;
when an ILP32 process (arch=RISCV32) makes a syscall, the cache returns ALLOW
without running the BPF filter, bypassing all arch-dispatch logic.

Define SECCOMP_ARCH_COMPAT = AUDIT_ARCH_RISCV32 so the cache maintains a
separate allow_compat bitmap for ILP32 processes.

[PATCH 3/3] kernel/seccomp.c: skip cache for ILP32 (TIF_32BIT) processes

Even with SECCOMP_ARCH_COMPAT defined, the allow_compat bitmap preparation
(seccomp_cache_prepare_bitmap) may incorrectly cache syscalls as always-allowed
for ILP32 processes.  Skip the cache entirely for processes with TIF_32BIT set
to ensure the BPF filter is always evaluated.

This is the simplest safe fix for the spike; a production kernel would want
to correctly populate allow_compat in seccomp_cache_prepare_bitmap instead.

Signed-off-by: Spike S <spike-s@fc32>
---
 arch/riscv/include/asm/syscall.h | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/riscv/include/asm/syscall.h b/arch/riscv/include/asm/syscall.h
index xxxxxxx..yyyyyyy 100644
--- a/arch/riscv/include/asm/syscall.h
+++ b/arch/riscv/include/asm/syscall.h
@@ -1,6 +1,11 @@
 static inline int syscall_get_arch(struct task_struct *task)
 {
 #ifdef CONFIG_64BIT
+#ifdef CONFIG_COMPAT
+	/* Check UXL in saved sstatus: SR_UXL_32 means 32-bit U-mode process.
+	 * Using task_pt_regs is more reliable than TIF_32BIT. */
+	if ((task_pt_regs(task)->status & SR_UXL) == SR_UXL_32)
+		return AUDIT_ARCH_RISCV32;
+#endif
 	return AUDIT_ARCH_RISCV64;
 #else
 	return AUDIT_ARCH_RISCV32;
